==English==

===Adverb===
'''blessedly'''

# In a [[blessed]] or [[holy]] manner. 
#:'''1599''' ''Therefore should every soldier in the wars do as every sick man in his bed, wash every mote out of his conscience; and dying so, death is to him advantage; or not dying, the time was '''blessedly''' lost wherein such preparation was gained''
#::— Shakespeare, ''Henry V'' [[s:The_Life_of_Henry_the_Fifth#SCENE_I._The_English_camp_at_Agincourt.|Act 4, Scene 1]]